                      USDA Nondiscrimination Statement

    The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) prohibits discrimination
    in all its programs and activities on the basis of race, color, national
    origin, gender, religion, age, disability, political beliefs, sexual
    orientation, and marital or family status. (Not all prohibited bases apply
    to all programs.)

   Persons with disabilities who require alternative means for
   communication of program information (Braille, large print, audiotape,
   etc.) should contact the USDA's TARGET Center at (202)720-2600 (voice
   and TDD).

   To file a complaint of discrimination, write:
   USDA, Director
   Office Of Civil Rights
   Room 326-W Whitten Building
   1400 Independence Avenue, SW
   Washington, DC 20250-9410

   or call (202)720-5964 (voice or TDD).

   USDA is an equal opportunity provider and employer.

